						<summary>

						<p>Two other fragments of a slab lying near the foot-path, east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It refers to the regime of Bahaduru Sultānu Muga[lāyi] and mentions one individual by name Yallāreḍḍi. It also refers to an enquiry into the revenue taxation in the village of Koṇḍūru. In characters of the 18th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
